## Agent-Oriented Failure Feedback

For custom checks, prefer failure messages with:

- what failed;
- why the project boundary or invariant matters;
- where an agent should look first to repair it;
- which evidence should be recorded after the fix.

## Rules

- A sensor is a signal, not a guarantee. It does not prove real-agent effectiveness.
- Do not run commands only because they appear here. Prefer repo-owned
  verification commands. If HarnessForge is available, use
  `harnessforge plan --target . --since HEAD` to choose relevant checks and
  `harnessforge verify --target . --run` when command execution is intended.
- Keep owner, source, purpose, and retire conditions current before promoting
  a check into release or automation gates.
- Remove or replace sensors that no longer catch meaningful regressions.
